Allow me to reintroduce myself with my utmost intentions. 

If you know me, you know I’ve poured my all into small businesses throughout my entire career.

Today, I want to ensure that you all know we launched FLOURYSH earlier this year. The platform is now THE Largest Premier Community-Driven Marketplace to Discover & Shop Black-owned Brands with over 150 founders and 6,000+ products. 

If you're a friend, former colleague, in corporate, looking to support small businesses, love me, [F] With Me...My ask is that you check out @WEFLOURYSH follow the page and check out all the amazing brands and products that we've curated just for you.

The Solution 👇🏾

1. Expecting fast results and not getting them will make you lose confidence. Never underestimate the power of patience.

2. If you experience failure always ask yourself “what was the reason for my failure? What can I learn from this and how can I improve?”

3. When not prepared for the unexpected don’t allow it to bring your world to a halt. 

4. Be prepared for boredom. Discipline is the difference between being great or being ordinary. 

5. Visualizing your dreams is powerful. Fuel your optimism and increase your motivation. 

6. Reason why we start, stop and then give up is because of the fear of the magnitude of the goal.  Focus of achieving the smaller day to day goals. 

#LifeHacks
#coaching

We had the distinct honor of partnering with TD Jakes Enterprises on a brand new venture Good Soil which was created to increase generational wealth and employment by supporting and nurturing Black entrepreneurs. We had the honor of inviting 23 dope Black-owned FLOURYSH partner brands to participate in our specially curated Marketplace.  It was beautiful to experience 2000 engaged and supportive attendees in the building not only there to water their soil for harvest but there to also spread seeds and hydrate others. 

Special Shout Out to our FLOURYSH family @DungeonForward who took home $100,000 after winning a very intense pitch competition and @annapookie for making the finals amongst 1000’s of applicants. 

I’d be remiss if I didn’t show love to Ebony and all the media outlets who supported the movement with action and coverage. 

Our FLOURYSH community is growing and true to our mission 

#FWitUs
#HustletoHarvest 
#GodsPlan
Good Soil provides the nutrients required for growth… Hard to harvest if your foundation isn’t right. My purpose in life is truly my love language.
